# Checkbox

`TxCheckbox` is a compact boolean control for settings, filters, and form rows. It exposes `role="checkbox"`, `aria-checked`, and disabled state, supports click / Enter / Space toggling, and only uses `aria-label` when no visible label or default slot is present.

## Basic Usage

Click the box or its label to toggle the state. The checked state follows the selected visual variant with either fill or tick motion.

### Checkbox
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="CheckboxCheckboxDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const checked = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxCheckbox v-model="checked" label="Option" />
  </template>
---
:::

## Variants

The default `fill` variant uses a pure filled square. Use `variant="checkmark"` when the checked state should include a stronger inner tick affordance.

### Checkbox variants
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="CheckboxCheckboxVariantsDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const fillChecked = ref(true)
  const checkmarkChecked = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <div style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 18px;">
      <TxCheckbox v-model="fillChecked" label="Fill style" />
      <TxCheckbox v-model="checkmarkChecked" variant="checkmark" label="With checkmark" />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

## Label First

Use `label-placement="start"` to render the visible label before the checkbox box.

### Checkbox (label start)
